commit.message:
event type fix and better AWS bounce setup instructions (#178)

* event type fix and better AWS bounce setup instructions

* update tests

Add AppConfig with verbose_name (#175)

The package will now appear as "Django SES" in admin panel instead
of "DJANGO_SES" or "Django_Ses".

Limit `requests` version for safety. Suggest installing `bounce` extra in case of missing packages. (#173)

* Added a `bounce` extra to `setup.py`.

This extra tracks the `requests` and `M2Crypto` packages as
dependencies, which are required for bounce message verification.

* Minor grammar edits

* Put an upper limit on the `requests` version for safety.

* Suggest installing django-ses with the `bounce` extra if any of the required packages is missing.

Added a `bounce` extra to `setup.py`. Fixes #171 (#172)

* Added a `bounce` extra to `setup.py`.

This extra tracks the `requests` and `M2Crypto` packages as
dependencies, which are required for bounce message verification.

* Minor grammar edits
Python 2 and 3 compatible bytes using future. Update test to catch this. (#167)

Excludes the "tests" directory from package (#163)

* exclude the tests directory from the bundled package

* Add a workaround for the corrupted /etc/boto.cfg and an explanation to tox.ini

Don't catch BaseExceptions (#161)

Exiting exceptions, such as `KeyboardInterrupt`, inherit from `BaseException` rather than `Exception`. The idiomatic way to catch any unexpected exception is to only catch `Exception`, so that `BaseExceptions` still bubble up.

Drop support for Django < 1.11, and add testing for Django 2.1 (#160)

* Drop support for Django < 1.11

* Add testing for Django 2.1

Remove obsolete syncdb instructions (#159)

Obsolete since 6bfea2d275398b94a414ac0a6a8cc0b6b75b9de1.

Fix #151, bounce message bytes. (#152)

* Fix #151, bounce message bytes.

* Always bytes in test

* Update per @blueyed feedback
